        "\\(dB = \\frac{\\mu_0 Idl\\sin\\theta}{4\\pi r^3}\\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "\\(dB = \\frac{\\mu_0 Idl\\sin\\theta}{4\\pi r^2}\\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Biot-Savart Law states \\( dB = \\frac{\\mu_0 I dl \\sin\\theta}{4\\pi r^2} \\), where \\( dB \\) is the magnetic field contribution, \\( I \\) is current, \\( dl \\) is length element, \\( r \\) is distance, and \\(\\theta\\) is the angle."
    },
